 Marx and Charles Darwin as from the messianism and utopianism of biblical and Kabbalistic works. Once described as a religion consisting of rituals, reason, and rabbinics, Judaism was now also rooted in land, labor, and bodies. Exhaustively researched, this original, revisionist account challenges our standard narratives of nationalism, secularization, and de-Judaization.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 20. Sep 2019) 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2018z978311063899840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300235586423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300235586.jpg  a978-3-11-063899-8  YUP eBook Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles